HEADWORD: outrigged
<hw>outrigged</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>rigged with a
structure projecting from or over the side of a boat for various
purposes; having an outrigger; -- to prevent capsizing or to support an
oarlock or to help secure a mast etc. See <er>outrigger</er></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

